Kitui Governor Julius Malombe has accused Senator David Musila of being a copycat and mimicking his plans and pronouncements.Both are running for governor.Malombe reacted fiercely to Musila&rsquo;s assertion that he will hire all ECDE teachers in Kitui on permanent and pensionable terms. He said that was his initial plan.&ldquo;Musila is only copying what I have planned. I have said that my government had already set aside money in the next budget to promote ECDE teachers to permanent terms next month [July], then he announces to do the same when he becomes governor,&rdquo; Malombe said. he spoke to journalists on Friday after addressing a Medium Term Plan meeting on Vision 2030 at the Kitui Kefri Centre.